Mob has to be 51+, but not all 51+ mobs summon.<br>
The mob will summon you if you reach the top of the hate list and you are out of melee range.<br>
There is a timer of a few seconds before a mob can summon again.<br>
Root is very effective against summoning mobs, since when rooted, whoever is closest to the mob remains at the top of the hate list, no matter what.<br>
There is some amount of damage that has to be done to the mob before it can summon, this allows for pulling of mobs and not have them summoning the puller.  I think once this damage has been done, the mob then can summon whomever reaches the top of the hate list.<br>
Sitting causes *additional* aggro, but if it's not enough to put you at the top of the hate list, you won't get summoned.<br>
<br>
To answer Saddil's questions:<br>
First question was answered above.<br>
